HEADWORD: Corndodger
<hw>Corn"dodg`er</hw> <pr>(k⟦ocir⟧rn"d?j`?r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
cake made of the meal of Indian corn, wrapped in a covering of husks or
paper, and baked under the embers.</def> <mark>[U.S.]</mark>
<rj><au>Bartlett.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

